Both the 2022 and the 2023 Form 10‑K for BNY Mellon disclose executive compensation “by reference” to the same proxy sections:  

* **Director Compensation** (under Item 1 – Election of Directors);  
* **Compensation Discussion & Analysis** and the **Executive Compensation Tables and Other Compensation Disclosures** (under Item 2 – Advisory Vote on Compensation);  
* **Board‑Meetings‑and‑Committee‑Information** – specifically the Committees and Committee Charters and the Human Resources and Compensation Committee (under Item 1 – Election of Directors – Corporate Governance and Board Information); and  
* the **Report of the HRC Committee**, which is deemed furnished.  

The 2023 filing repeats this exact set of references, with only minor wording changes (e.g., using “&” and adding a hyphen after “Item 2”). Thus, the structure of the executive‑compensation disclosure has not materially changed between 2022 and 2023; BK continues to incorporate the same proxy‑referenced sections for its “Other Compensation Disclosures.”
